    "en": {
      "title": "A record high temperature for the UK",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Temperatures in Britain have soared above 40 degrees Celsius (104 degrees Fahrenheit) for the first time, and the historic day marks a rise in the death toll from high temperatures, a rise in bushfires and disruption to travel.",
        "Heathrow Airport recorded a temperature of 40.2 degrees Celsius at 12.50pm on Tuesday, officially the hottest day ever.",
        "This has already been considered as a national emergency, and foreign reports say that the unprecedented heat wave made the situation in the country's capital unbearable on Tuesday.",
        "Meanwhile, heatwaves have killed hundreds of people in Spain and Portugal over the past week as Europe battles temperatures of more than 40C.",
        "In Spain, between July 10 and July 16, 510 people were affected by the heat wave, according to the country's health departments."
      ],
